						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Food-security/Related-developments/Population-boom-poses-interconnected-challenges-of-energy-food-water" title="Population boom poses interconnected challenges of energy, food, water" alt="link">Population boom poses interconnected challenges of energy, food, water</a></h2>

	
					<p>Speakers at ‘The Interconnected World of Energy, Food and Water’ international symposium called for innovations in plant biotechnology, synthetic biology and information technology to address the challenges of a growing world population. The discussion aimed at fostering greater awareness among scientists, the public and policy-makers about the interconnections between the three challenges. Regarding regulatory policies for example, there is a pressing need to keep pace with technology development and deployment, and to build science-based risk assessment capability and consumer confidence. (via<a href="http://www.eurekalert.org/pub_releases/2013-04/acs-pbp031213.php?utm_source=K4DNewsletterEN&amp;utm_medium=Link&amp;utm_campaign=K4D_EN_April2013" target="_self"> EurekAlert</a>, 8/04/2013)</p>
							<p><span class="date">22/05/2013</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Food-security/Related-developments/Population-boom-poses-interconnected-challenges-of-energy-food-water">Read more...</a>
</div>
